plores both the practicalities and the therapeutic processes that come into play in an outdoor natural setting. The book will be of use to counsellors, psychotherapists, arts therapists, psychologists and health professionals who are interested in taking their therapeutic work into natural environments and outdoor spaces. "--cProvided by publisher.  a16 0aCounseling. 0aPsychotherapy.  aBF 636.6 J67 2015c1hUAAU-Bi0162035212677  aBF 636.6 J67 2015wLCc1i0162035212677d1/30/2017e1/30/2017kCHECKEDOUTlON_SHELFmUAAUGn4p$150.00rMsYtBOOKu1/9/201501ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n2014025770bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/308232747